Two charred bodies were found in a double-cab bakkie in the Free State at the weekend, police said. Police were  investigating a stock theft incident in Selosesha in Thaba Nchu when they discovered the bodies, spokesperson Brig Motantsi Makhele said. Makhele said the charred bodies were found in the burnt out  bakkie under several trees. “The two bodies are unknown and it can't be determined at this stage whether it's males or females.” An inquest docket had been opened.